Date:  8/4/1853
Source:  Traveller under Concern
Author:  MACKIE
Vol / Page:  99
Edition:  19I73
Quote:  Standing by our inn I heard a noise like the howling of dogs and asking a man who was passing what it was, he told us that it was the Maories at their pa .. howling or crying on acount of the death of one of their number, they call it `tangitary', wailing for the dead.
